x4freetext: Scandium, iron and silicon  filters were used
2 keV- Si of 258g/cm**2 thickness, B(4)C of 0.3g/cm**2,
FWHM 0.8 keV, neutron beam at 1 m distance from filter
55 keV- Si of 200g/cm**2, S of 41g/cm**, B-10 of
0.2g/cm**2, FWHM 2.keV, neutron beam at 1 m distance
144 keV - Si of 200g/cm**2, Ti of 6.8g/cm**, B-10 of
0.2 g/cm**2, FWHM 25.keV, neutron beam at 1 m distance
Hydrogen counter SNM-38 for EN 144 and 55 keV,
Differential and total c-s were derived relative to
scattering c-s of lead, which was defined as difference
total c-s ( obtained in transmission measurement) and
and capture c-s from REL-REF of D.I.Gerber+.
